text: Amirovo () is a rural locality (a village) in Maysky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 26 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 64 km from Iglino, 7 km from Maysky. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Amirovo, Iglinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
